**This took a lot of effort to document. Please upvote if helpful**

**Method-1**
Most elementary method is by creating a  copy of given array and exploiting defn of rotation: *nums[(i+k)%n] = old_nums[i]*.
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)
```
class Solution {
public:
    void rotate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n=nums.size();
        vector<int> cpy(nums.cbegin(), nums.cend());

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            nums[(i+k)%n] = cpy[i];
        }
    }
};
```

**Method-2**
Here, we reduce the space complexity from O(n) to O(1). Note that the rotated array consists of two parts of the main array- one from [k..n-1], and otehr from [0..k-1]. Note that the part from [0..k-1] follows [k..n-1]. So, we reverse the main array, and re-reverse it in two parts- [0..k-1] and [k..n-1].
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
```
class Solution {
public:
    void rotate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        k %= n;

        reverse(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        reverse(nums.begin(), nums.begin()+k);
        reverse(nums.begin()+k, nums.end());

        return;
    }
};
```

**Method-3**
This is fairly mathematically involved, and some interest in number theory is expected. Although it too used O(n) space, but instead of storing *n integers*, we store *n booleans*; also this is mainly for mathematic interests. For *n*, and *k*, we have two cases-
Case i: *gcd(n,k) = 1*
S = {(i+k)%n | i=0 or i \in S} = {i | 0<=i and i<n}
Case ii: *gcd(n,k) = d != 1*
St = {(i+k)%n | i=t or i \in S}; union of whom for t=0 to t=d-1, will equal {i | 0<=i and i<n}.
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)
```
class Solution {
public:
    void rotate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        k %= n;
        vector<bool> visited(n, false);

        int curr_idx = 0, curr_val = nums[0], next_idx = k;
        for (int i = 0; i < n;i++) {
            if (!visited[i]) {
                curr_idx = i;
                next_idx = (i + k) % n;
                curr_val = nums[i];
                while (!visited[next_idx]) {
                    visited[next_idx] = true;
                    swap(curr_val, nums[next_idx]);
                    curr_idx = next_idx;
                    next_idx = (curr_idx + k) % n;
                }
            }
        }
    }
};
```

