# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Divide the array into two parts, one ranging from 0 to n-k-1 and the other ranging from n-k to n-1. Afterward, reverse the first and second parts of the array and finally reverse the entire array to obtain the result
# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

