var rotate = function(nums, k) {
    if(k === 0) return nums
    let rotations = k % nums.length
    let tempArr = nums.splice(nums.length - rotations, rotations)
    return nums.unshift(...tempArr)
};
```

Get remainder of k % nums.length, to get rid of all full-rotations you would have to do for bigger values.

Take out the amount of rotations you have remaining from the back of the nums array.
Store in temporary array with original order intact thanks to splice().

Insert it all back into the front of the original array with the temporary array.

